  "text": "After depletion, DCs in lymphoid tissues of DTR ϩ mice recover to predepletion levels within several days, [CITATION_1] whereas in the bladder, recovery is slower. [CITATION_2] Repopulation of the LC intima in the ascending aortic arch by CD11c ϩ DCs was determined at different times after DT treatment by en face immunostaining. More than 600 CD11c ϩ DCs were identified in undepleted controls (PBS-injected DTR ϩ mice and DT-injected DTR Ϫ mice) ( Figure 5A ). At 24 hours, Ͻ10 DCs were identified, which represents Ͼ98% depletion. Gradually, DC numbers increased, with approximately 25% and 75% recovery at 7 and 21 days, respectively.",
